long); entirely brown dorsally except for 4 median orange spots on the pronotum; deflexed elytral apex somewhat truncate along margin B with margin C slightly sinuate; distinguished most obviously from 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFE7FBA88FDCEE8D9" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[391,536,1435,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Trisinuata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFE7FBA88FDCEE8D9" box="[391,536,1435,1458]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Tri. papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of the deflexed elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E74C53BFF3FBAACFED6EB0C" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E74C53BFF3FBAACFED6EB0C" blockId="118.[151,1436,1182,1639]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFF3FBAACFEEDE8BC" bold="true" box="[199,315,1471,1495]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Remarks.</emphasis>
This study extends the number of males known in collections. 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFBBABAADFAB5E8BD" authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier. McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[1090,1379,1470,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFBBABAADFAD1E8BD" box="[1090,1287,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Luciola papuana</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
was described from a female coloured like 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFDA5BAF0FD36E891" box="[605,736,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFDA5BAF0FD0AE891" authorityName="McDermott" authorityYear="1959" box="[605,732,1507,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuae">M. papuae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Males lacking the deflexed elytral apex are associated with 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFF6FB915FE80EB75" authorityName="Olivier. McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,342,1542,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuana">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFF6FB915FE80EB75" box="[151,342,1542,1566]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Luciola papuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the species assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFD61B914FCDAEB75" authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[665,780,1543,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Trisinuata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFD61B914FCDAEB75" box="[665,780,1543,1566]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Trisinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFCEDB914FCA9EB74" bold="true" box="[789,895,1543,1567]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="458122695E74C53BFCEDB914FCA9EB74" box="[789,895,1543,1567]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and redescribed below. 
<tableCitation id="214476BB5E74C53BFB6BB915FB31EB75" box="[1171,1255,1542,1566]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="54.[151,239,295,319]" captionText="TABLE 9. Luciolinae males with dark brown, grey or black dorsal colouration." pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Table 9</tableCitation>
lists 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFADCB915FA4AEB75" authorityName="sensu McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[1316,1436,1542,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciolinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Luciolinae</taxonomicName>
sharing similar pale brown dorsal colouration, of which three species, including this one, are assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFAD1B938FA4AEB29" authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[1321,1436,1579,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Trisinuata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFAD1B938FA4AEB29" box="[1321,1436,1579,1602]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Trisinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFF6FB95CFED6EB0C" bold="true" box="[151,256,1615,1639]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="458122695E74C53BFF6FB95CFED6EB0C" box="[151,256,1615,1639]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
